<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-603-875  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 603 875.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  Nov 5 1990 v7 n13 p49(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Managing LAN documents is increasingly complex: but good softwarepackages make the task easier. (tutorial)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Edelman, Russ.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The explosive growth of local area networks (LANs) has madespecial software for file and document management imperative.andP;  Ona LAN, a document is essentially a file created by an application.andO;Document management software facilitates the organization andmanagement of such files.andP;  Document management software addressesseven areas: profiling, the creation of identifying informationabout the document; searching, the ability to locate informationin the document or its profile; management utilities that allowdefinition of the tables used to create the profile; filemanagement, which archives and restores information on a regularbasis; resource accounting, tracking and recording systemresources used by a given document; importation utilities thatfacilitate the incorporation of pre-existing files into thedocument management package; and computer platform compatibility.andO;The document management packages PC DOCS, PerfectSolution, andProfound are compared for their functioning in several of theseareas.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Document Management SystemsLocal Area NetworksTutorialFile Management.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>